<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-02-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-02-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="352" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d352">
                    <head>No. 1065.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Straus</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-02-21"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 21,
                            1888</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 74.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your dispatch No. 57, of the
                        28th ultimo, relative to the prohibition against foreign Jews settling in
                        Jerusalem, and desire to approve your reported action in respect of American
                        citizens of that faith residing there as discreet and proper.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>